#
# Polytonic and other greek-related glyphs
# INFO: These are to be used while using a (modern) greek layout.
# INFO: Actions are used only as prefixes.
#
# actions (in order, prefixed to the letter):
#
#   either:
#     ad/subscript (pros/ypogegrammeni): ι
#     breathing (psili dasia): > <
#     diaeresis (dialytika): "
#     accent (tonos oxia varia varia perispomeni): ' / \ ` ^
#   or:
#     macron breve: _ -
#   or:
#     caron: ω (v key)
#
# standalone symbols of diacretics and decorations
#   ⸒  # hypodiastole
#   ͺ  # hypogegrammene
#   ι  # prosgegrammene
#   ·  # ano teleia
#   ΄  # tonos
#   ῀  # perispomene
#   `  # varia
#   ´  # oxia
#   ¨  # dialytika (diaeresis)
#   ΅  # dialytika tonos
#   ῁  # dialytika perispomene
#   ῭  # dialytika varia
#   ΅  # dialytika oxia
#   ῏  # psili perispomene
#   ῍  # psili varia
#   ῎  # psili oxia
#   ῟  # dasia perispomene
#   ῝  # dasia varia
#   ῞  # dasia oxia

